                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14073431" author="tilman" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2014 17:51:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For some reason, SampledImageReader.getRGBImage() has returned a RGBA images instead of an RGB image. So I&apos;ve expanded the array to accept 4 entries in rev 1613204. However I wonder why SampledImageReader.getRGBImage() returns an RGBA image - PDFBox bug or buggy PDF? &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; could you have a look at this?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14073438" author="tilman" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2014 17:59:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SampledImageReader.getRGBImage() returns a RGBA image if the colorKey param isn&apos;t null.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;  /Name /Im2
  /Type /XObject
  /Length 21 0 R
  /Filter /FlateDecode
  /Subtype /Image
  /Width 88
  /Height 87
  /BitsPerComponent 8
  /ColorSpace /DeviceRGB
  /Mask [255 255 255 255 255 255]   &amp;lt;=== &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; is it
  /SMask 16 0 R
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14074881" author="jahewson" created="Fri, 25 Jul 2014 20:44:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &quot;RGB&quot; in &quot;getRGBImage&quot; refers to the color space rather than the exact image format, this behaviour is explained in the JavaDoc:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Returns the content of the given image as an AWT buffered image with an RGB color space. If a color key mask is provided then an ARGB image is returned instead.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The image is either RGB or ARGB. Color key masks are very rare and images use a lot of memory and CPU time, especially alpha channels, so we only use ARGB is we really have to.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT: The bug fix looks good to me, I&apos;ll mark this issue as Fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
